eturn-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2530886\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Aug 16, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104peh1665702976668.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/peh1665702976668.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/peh1665702976668.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"peh1665702976668\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Packing Code to DBMS Storage Format Mappings\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Uniface automatically maps model-level packing codes to connector-level packing codes, so the connector only needs to be aware of the connector-level packing codes.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"peh1665702976668__p_d62093e1_d62094e1_d62095e1\">This mapping:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"peh1665702976668__li_d27161e1_d27162e1_d27163e1\">Enables the connector to restrict the number of packing codes that it supports, without restricting the portability of Uniface applications.\n <p class=\"p\" id=\"peh1665702976668__p_d62096e1_d62097e1_d62098e1\">At the model-level, the application designer has a choice of several hundred combinations of Uniface data type and packing code for every field definition.</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"peh1665702976668__li_d27164e1_d27165e1_d27166e1\">Reduces the complexity of the connector by mapping model-level packing codes to preferred connector-level packing codes.\n <p class=\"p\" id=\"peh1665702976668__p_d62099e1_d62100e1_d62101e1\">The connector does not generally need to perform data conversions, since it only supports the packing codes that correspond directly to a DBMS storage format. Uniface handles the conversion for you.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"peh1665702976668__p_d62102e1_d62103e1_d62104e1\">There is a distinction between original connector-level packing codes and redefined connector-level packing codes. The connector must specify a mapping table in <code class=\"ph codeph\">uinfo-&gt;upfmt[]</code> in the Info connector request. This table specifies the mapping from original connector- level packing codes to redefined connector-level packing codes.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"peh1665702976668__p_d62105e1_d62106e1_d62107e1\">Every DBMS connector is responsible for mapping the redefined connector-level packing codes to storage formats recognized by the API of the DBMS. The following illustration shows the complete mapping process:</p>\n<figure class=\"fig fignone\" id=\"peh1665702976668__fig_d62108e1_d62109e1_d62110e1\">\n<div class=\"p\">\n<figure class=\"fig fignone\" id=\"peh1665702976668__fig_w3950ab1b5b9b1b1_w3951ab1b5b9b1_w3952ab1b5b9_w3953ab1b5_w3954ab1\">\n<img alt=\"Flow of mapping level from modeled entity to DBMS internal storage format\" class=\"image\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/packingcodemappingprocess2.jpg?_LANG=enus\"/>\n</figure>\n</div>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"peh1665702976668__p_d62111e1_d62112e1_d62113e1\">For the application designer, the illustrated process is invisible. In the rest of the Uniface documentation, there is no distinction made between the application model-level packing codes and the connector-level packing codes.</p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"peh1665702976668__section_wds_2d3_kcc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1052893e95\">More Information</h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"peh1665702976668__ul_aw2_fd3_kcc\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"peh1665702976668__li_d27167e1_d27168e1_d27169e1\">For packing code mappings of the DBMS connectors\n               Uniface provides, see the appropriate connector documentation in <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"lsp1665702531534.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/lsp1665702531534.html\" title=\"To access, retrieve, and store data, Uniface provides database connectors that translate Uniface I/O requests into the target database's data definition and manipulation languages.\">Database Connectors</a>. </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"peh1665702976668__li_d27170e1_d27171e1_d27172e1\">For connector-level packing codes, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"buy1665702976826.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/buy1665702976826.html\" title=\"The symbolic values for the connector level packing codes are defined in the unidbm.h include file provided by Uniface.\">Connector-Level Packing Codes</a>. </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"peh1665702976668__li_d27173e1_d27174e1_d27175e1\">For possible redefinitions of connector-level\n               packing codes, see the <code class=\"ph codeph\">uinfo-&gt;upfmt</code> field in <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"iga1665702915956.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/iga1665702915956.html\" title=\"Supplies Uniface with basic information about the DBMS and the connector.\">uinfo</a>. </li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2530886\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2530886\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Packing Code to DBMS Storage Format Mappings Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Aug 16, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Packing Code to DBMS Storage Format Mappings Uniface automatically maps model-level packing codes to connector-level packing codes, so the connector only needs to be aware of the connector-level packing codes. This mapping: Enables the connector to restrict the number of packing codes that it supports, without restricting the portability of Uniface applications. At the model-level, the application designer has a choice of several hundred combinations of Uniface data type and packing code for every field definition. Reduces the complexity of the connector by mapping model-level packing codes to preferred connector-level packing codes. The connector does not generally need to perform data conversions, since it only supports the packing codes that correspond directly to a DBMS storage format. Uniface handles the conversion for you. There is a distinction between original connector-level packing codes and redefined connector-level packing codes. The connector must specify a mapping table in uinfo->upfmt[] in the Info connector request. This table specifies the mapping from original connector- level packing codes to redefined connector-level packing codes. Every DBMS connector is responsible for mapping the redefined connector-level packing codes to storage formats recognized by the API of the DBMS. The following illustration shows the complete mapping process: For the application designer, the illustrated process is invisible. In the rest of the Uniface documentation, there is no distinction made between the application model-level packing codes and the connector-level packing codes. More Information For packing code mappings of the DBMS connectors Uniface provides, see the appropriate connector documentation in Database Connectors . For connector-level packing codes, see Connector-Level Packing Codes . For possible redefinitions of connector-level packing codes, see the uinfo->upfmt field in uinfo . Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}